setup:
A developer needs to track how many characters a user has typed into a text field and show it in real-time. They write:

```js
input.addEventListener('change', function() {
  counter.textContent = input.value.length;
});
```

The counter only updates after the user clicks away from the field, not while typing.

You have a button with this handler:

```js
button.addEventListener('click', () => {
  console.log('A');
});

button.addEventListener('click', () => {
  console.log('B');
});
```
